Results.ReviewText: Opening a jar of Nescafe Gold used to be like walking past a coffee shop roasting coffee baens - now it smells of nothing, is more bitter and leaves a gritty residue - yes I know it is finely ground beans but let's have the old recipe back as well as the new fangled backward step!
Results.Title: Ruined a good coffee

Results.ReviewText: Sometimes, coffee can leave you with a bitter taste. Nescafe Gold Blend leaves a good taste behind with none of the bitterness. My tip is to put the granules in your cup, add some cold milk and whisk with a hand whisk to froth it up a little and then add boiled water. Is so good.
Results.Title: Smooth Taste without the bitterness

Results.ReviewText: I’ve been drinking Nescafé instant coffee for many years and I was very happy with the quality and taste of the regular blend, however now that I’ve discovered the Gold blend my life has got even better, one cup first thing in the morning really sets me up for the morning ahead.
Results.Title: Excellent wake me up juice!

Results.ReviewText: OMG!!!  What have you done. My family & I have been drinking & loving Nescafe Gold ever since it same out...but not any more . The 'New'  Nescafe Gold is awful, much Stronger Leaves a nasty taste in the mouth & horrible residue in the cup. I will be changing my Brand from now on
Results.Title: OMG What have you done!!!

Results.ReviewText: Always buy Gold as this I have grown up with and when they change the coffee it only seems to get better. So rich and smooth have not found another coffee that makes my tastebuds feel like they have gone to heaven. Keep making this coffee and I will never give up buying this :D
Results.Title: The Perfect Perk Up in the morning and all day

Results.ReviewText: Over the years I have tried many brands of instant coffee but always return to Nescafe Gold Blend.  I love the smooth taste and consistant quality.  The price is on par with other coffees.  If you want a real treat have a "friendly" coffee by adding a shot of brandy or whiskey.
Results.Title: Simply the Best

Results.ReviewText: I was recently offered Nescafe Gold Blend at an elderly aunt's house !  I normally drink Nescafe original (and other brands) but it was so good that I bought a jar which now sits handily beside my Nescafe original........so depending in my mood ....I decide which coffee I want
Results.Title: Smooth as Silk

Results.ReviewText: Rarely do I have more than one or two cups of coffee a day, that's why I enjoy looking forward to the smooth rich taste of Nescafe Gold Blend. You can count on its taste every time whether enjoying it black or with milk on your own or with friends. Never any need to add sugar.
Results.Title: The smoothest cup of coffee

Results.ReviewText: I used to buy nescafe years ago. But the taste seemed to change so I changed to a different brand. But when I tasted Nescafe Gold again, I was astounded. That taste was back and even better. It's smoother, it's in a decaff, and it's fab. Hurrah, Nescafe is back in my cupboard.

Results.ReviewText: Please please please bring back the old gold blend, it was so much better than the one you have changed it too. I have drunk gold blend for a very long time and have always wished I could buy a cup in a coffee shop. Now I can’t even get it at home. Might have to resort to tea.

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe. We really appreciate your feedback! Results.ReviewText: Goodbye Nescafe and Gold Blend. If and when you come to your senses and revert to the original recipe I will come back. What was the "gold standard" of instant coffee is now a bland cup of brown sludge. It now tastes disgusting, smells dreadful and leaves a bitter aftertaste.

Results.ReviewText: I brought this coffee from Sainsbury and I have stocked up on four more. This blend is smooth and the coffee does not have a bitter after taste. I tend to add a teaspoon and a bit and this goes well with just a teaspoon of coffee. I would highly recommend it for coffee lovers
Results.Title: Perfect Coffee blend

Results.ReviewText: Nescafe have pulled off the difficult task of not only setting the gold standard for taste and quality in instant coffee but constantly raising the bar. Gold Blend gets better and better, with an even smoother and richer taste whilst continuing to offer great value for money.

I've also use it in cakes to obtain a mild coffee flavour, just add a small amount of water or milk to disolve and add to mixture.
Good value for money if you buy the larger jar.
